          <div class="pd-meta">Step 01 · Understand</div>
          <h3>Discovery</h3>
          <p>We learn your business, goals, audience, and constraints — and define what success actually looks like. This is a conversation, not a sales call. We map the problem before touching the solution.</p>
          <div class="pd-deliv">
            <span>Goals workshop</span><span>Audit of current setup</span><span>Success metrics</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="pd-step" data-reveal data-d="1">
        <div class="pd-marker">02</div>
        <div class="pd-body">
          <div class="pd-meta">Step 02 · Scope</div>
          <h3>Planning</h3>
          <p>A fixed scope, timeline, and architecture you sign off before a line of code is written. You see exactly what's being built, in what order, and what it costs. No hourly surprises.</p>
          <div class="pd-deliv">
            <span>Fixed-scope proposal</span><span>Sitemap / flow</span><span>Timeline</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="pd-step" data-reveal data-d="2">
        <div class="pd-marker">03</div>
        <div class="pd-body">
          <div class="pd-meta">Step 03 · Shape</div>
          <h3>Design</h3>
          <p>Layouts and systems designed around outcomes — not trends. We work in rounds so the design sharpens with your input before development begins. Mobile, accessibility, and performance are considered from the first wireframe.</p>
          <div class="pd-deliv">
            <span>Wireframes</span><span>Visual design</span><span>Design system</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="pd-step" data-reveal data-d="3">
        <div class="pd-marker">04</div>
        <div class="pd-body">
          <div class="pd-meta">Step 04 · Build</div>
          <h3>Development</h3>
          <p>Hand-coded, tested, and reviewed against the standard. No page builders, no shortcuts. Clean, documented code that loads fast and is easy for anyone to maintain later.</p>
          <div class="pd-deliv">
            <span>Hand-coded build</span><span>Cross-browser QA</span><span>Performance pass</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="pd-step" data-reveal data-d="4">
        <div class="pd-marker">05</div>
        <div class="pd-body">
          <div class="pd-meta">Step 05 · Connect</div>
          <h3>Automation</h3>
          <p>Workflows are built, monitored, and documented so you understand exactly what runs, when, and why. Every node is testable, and nothing goes live without a dry run against real data.</p>
          <div class="pd-deliv">
            <span>Workflow build</span><span>Monitoring</span><span>Documentation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>

